     1→//! Claude Code adapter — spawns and manages Claude Code sessions via PTY.
     2→//!
     3→//! Launches `claude --output-format stream-json` in a pseudo-terminal,
     4→//! streams structured JSONL output to the daemon event channel, and
     5→//! injects keystrokes for input. Approval requests are surfaced as
     6→//! [`DaemonMessage::ApprovalRequest`] so the web UI can render buttons.
     7→
     8→use std::collections::HashMap;
     9→use std::sync::Arc;
    10→
    11→use async_trait::async_trait;
    12→use chrono::Utc;
    13→use life_relay_core::{
